



Gentn
Mount Vernon Feby 20th 1772



On the 25th of last Month I drew upon you in favour of the Revd Mr Boucher, Tutor to Mr Custis, for Fifty pounds Sterling which please to pay and place to the Acct of this young Gentlemen.1
I have been impatiently waiting for my Goods, being much in want of the Millstones, having heard nothing from you in respect
[16]
to them since the 12th of Septr though Captn Montgomerie (immediately from London in about Eight Weeks Passage) arrived in this River about the first of JanuaryI hope to receive them by Walker who I understand is daily expected2 and am Gentn Yr Most Hble Servt

Go: Washington

